race.description: Stacks Law Firm Super Showcase Mdn Plate
race.comment: TALK ABOUT LAYLA (14) started at generous odds but defied the market on debut last start, making late ground to be beaten under a length over 1312m at this track. Only needs to exhibit a little natural improvement to be opening her account. DEVOTED TO YOU (8) was always behind the eight-ball after missing the start here last start. Fitter for two runs back from a spell. Draws ideally so with better gate manners today she can figure in the finish. PRIZE WITNESS (13) was a long way off the pace when they straightened last start then she made good late ground, an impressive enough debut over 1200m at Newcastle. Comes right into contention out to this more favourable journey. CARMINE (1) has been runner-up in both starts to date, with each of those maidens throwing up multiple subsequent winners. Draws the fence and the blinkers go on so expect him to be very popular with punters. TAKE A BREAK (5) is next pick with winkers on for the first time.
